When hiking now I slather on an SPF 50+, add a hat and glasses!

Our skin is our largest organ and after all I’ve been through I’m going to treat it right!

Side note, even if you’re home or driving, always wear your spf!

From there I’m finding monthly laser, facials and peels are also keeping my skin in top condition! In fact as I write this I’m in the middle of looking like a snake 🐍 from a @vipeel . More to come on that…

My great uncle Frank Westmore explaining how my grandfather Monte made Vivien Leigh’s hazel eyes appear green in Gone with the Wind. 💄
•
My grandfather was working on 3 movie (Intermezzo, Rebecca and Gone With The Wind) simultaneously as the head makeup supervisor. 📽️
•
David Selznick, the film producer, would send multiple pages of memos and call my grandfather at all hours of the night to make last minute changes to the makeup and wardrobe. 
•
As the story goes, The stress from the workload led to my grandfather’s fatal heart attack at the age of 37. My dad was barely 2 years old.

👄Did you know the skin on your lips is the thinnest skin on your body?? 🤯 
.
One big difference is that your lips don't have sebaceous glands.
Those little guys keep the skin on the rest of your body moisturized, but your lips, Help! They are on their own!
The only source of help they get is from your saliva, and that's why they become dry and chapped and over time look older. 
.
Because of this and many other reasons, it’s important to infuse your lips with the right ingredients all year round but especially during the dry winter months!
.
My @westmorebeauty 60 second lip effect was an important creation for me to not just plump, firm and anti-age the lips but infuse that hydration we all need day & night with ingredients like Shea butter, squalane, vitamin E, sodium hyaluronate and bakuchiol! This is one lip product that’s like a spa treatment at home! 🧖‍♀️

My great grandfather George met actress Billie Burke who needed a hair lace wig for an upcoming show for Triangle Studio, which he sewed and delivered the next day.
•
After Billie tried on the wig, George offered to apply her makeup, as at the time there were no makeup artists—actors did their own makeup. 
•
He then noticed that her eyelashes were a bit sparse, so he clipped tiny pieces of hair from her wig and pasted them to each of her lashes, thus creating the very first pair of individual false eyelashes! 
•
Triangle Studio was so impressed with my great grandfather’s work that they offered him a full-time position to set up his own division, creating the first makeup department at a movie studio at $150 a week. This connection would later lead him to work with another rising star at the time Douglas Fairbanks.
•
What I am most proud of is taking all my family’s history and formulating each @WestmoreBeauty product to give the Hollywood effects my family has been delivering for over 100 years 💄🤩
